website_summaries.verdict: A pricier treat, but its pure meaty and chewy composition is sure to grab and hold any dog’s attention for as long as you need it.
pros: Free-range lamb is the first ingredient
Easy to break into smaller pieces
cons: One of the most expensive training treats available

customer_reviews.title: My dogs love this stuff!
customer_reviews.text: I discovered this product when one of my dog's was getting physical therapy and they used pieces of this jerky to get her to continue walking in the underwater treadmill, like dangling the proverbial carrot. Been buying it ever since (over 3 years now) because it's such high quality, but first time buying on Amazon. This bag was nice and pliable, easy to break or tear into pieces. I've bought some bags locally that were way too tough and very difficult to break and it didn't look like it was easy to chew either. I have small dogs so they need smaller pieces. Will buy again ... unless you raise the prices like crazy so please don't do that.
customer_reviews.author: ellemac

customer_reviews.title: High Value Training Treat!
customer_reviews.text: We bought a couple bags of these from our training center and our dogs loved them so much, I was happy to see amazon sold bigger bags! Have tried the beef and Venison/Liver flavors so far with the dogs and they love them both, but the beef ones are easier to break apart. After a couple weeks, the Venison flavor got really tough like jerky. Our dogs have sensitive stomachs and they both love love love these, we use every weekend for training and no poop problems or gas that we’ve noticed.
customer_reviews.author: Jessica Shaltz

customer_reviews.title: Delicious and healthy
customer_reviews.text: Wonderfully healthy ingredients for my dog. She loves eating these. They are thin enough that you can break them in half or thirds to use while training. They have a texture like jerky, but not as dry. I like this flavor because my dog can have a taste of other meats that are too expensive to feed often. I have purchased these numerous times.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Great product, too bad about the seller
customer_reviews.text: I have used these treaty’s for 15 years with my dogs. One of the few pet treats that does not contain rosemary, a good thing. Unfortunately this seller will only send these in a padded mailer. So instead of the treats you ordered, you get crumbs. Useless. I will be purchasing this great product from another seller.
customer_reviews.author: madameleota

customer_reviews.title: Our dog loves these!
customer_reviews.text: I love the real meat company products for their minimal ingredients and the size of treat. The treat can be give as one large piece or easily broken down into small pieces providing lots of treat. I have had trouble with the beef flavor breaking apart so usually order lamb and liver or one of their other flavors. I also love that their are moist treats but don't leave your hands slimy.
customer_reviews.author: KP

customer_reviews.title: The only dog treats that don't give my dog bad gas
customer_reviews.text: A little pricey, but my dog loves them. The bag is tall, but thin. I break the treats into smaller pieces for training. These are the only treats that don't cause bad meatloaf smelling dog farts

customer_reviews.title: My dog loves them ❤️

customer_reviews.title: Great treats for a picky dog
customer_reviews.text: These jerky treats are my dog's favorite treats. Recently my vet stopped selling them and I panicked for a few seconds. I had the realization: "I can check Amazon!". Truthfully, this is the closest you can get to giving your dog jerky. My vet is a holistic vet and I consequently don't give my dog just any treat. Still, my tiny toy poodle is VERY particular, even to the point of knowing which flavor he wants when I hold up the bags! I bought the lamb liver, chicken and venison and venison but he loves all of the flavors, even the fish. I like the fact that they are all natural and I'd recommend them in a heartbeat.
